-- NFL Season-Opening Game Delayed by Lightning Threat in Denver
-- B y   D e x   M c L u s k e y
-- 2013-09-06T00:56:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-06/nfl-season-opening-game-delayed-by-lightning-threat-in-denver.html
The start of the opening game of the
National Football League regular season has been delayed by the
threat of lightning in Denver.  The game between the Broncos and the Super Bowl champion
 Baltimore Ravens  at Sports Authority Field at Mile High was
scheduled to begin at 6:30 p.m. local time.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dex McLuskey at 
 dmcluskey@bloomberg.net  